@laanwj I was looking into cppcheck and cpplint the last days. It was trivial to set up. According to the tools, those are the last unused variables.

Also, they found a ton of unused functions, but I couldn't find anything that deserves attention. E.g. [DeleteAuthCookie](https://dev.visucore.com/bitcoin/doxygen/rpc_2protocol_8cpp.html#a9807259ee7b7c4f5445cf54fd23589cb) is unused, but there is no point in removing the code. Almost all unused functions potentially turn out to be useful in the future.

Finally, cppcheck returned some errors and warnings but my knowledge of cpp is too low. So they could very well be false positives.
